{"word":"ἀρκτέος","slug":"ἀρκτέος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἀρκτέος</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:verbal Adjective'>verb. <a href='S:Adjective'>adj.</a></a> of <el>ἄρχομαι</el>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>one must begin</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:verbal Adjective'>verb. <a href='S:Adjective'>adj.</a></a> of <el>ἄρχω</el>, <i>one must govern</i>; and in pass sense, <i>one must be ruled</i>, <a href='S:id est'>i.e.</a> <i>obey</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}